\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Local Area	
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf4 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 The house is 15 minutes from Mexico\'92s national park and observatory and 40 minutes from San Quintin\'92s ancient volcanoes and Oyster Bay - $5 for 20 Amazing!, Fishing boats head out to Isla San Martin for world-class fishing from San Quintin, Call and book a trip - $500 x4 people for the day.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Local fishermen head out right in front of the house most mornings and offer fresh catches at unbeatable prices\'97get there around 10 a.m. and strike a deal.\
For the best tacos in town, check out Pericos at the end of town\'97look for the orange building with smoke billowing from a custom-built grill. It\'92s a must-try!\
A trip to Oyster Bay in San Quintin is a must, where you can get 20 oysters shucked or BBQ'd for just $5.\
On Fridays, there\'92s a popular Oaxaca market 25 minutes south in Vicente Guerrero.\
